a Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Via Latin <i>Gregorius</i> from the post-classical Greek name <i>Gregōrios</i> ‘watchful’ (a derivative of <i>gregōrein</i> ‘to watch, be vigilant’). The name was a very popular one among the early Christians, who were mindful of the injunction ‘be sober, be vigilant’ (1 Peter 5:8). It was borne by a number of early saints. The most important, in honour of whom the name was often bestowed from medieval times onwards, were Gregory of Nazianzen (  <i>c.</i>329–90 ), Gregory of Nyssa (  d. <i>c.</i>395 ), Gregory of Tours (  538–94 ), and  Pope Gregory the Great  (  <i>c.</i>540–604 ). A famous bearer of the name in modern times is the film star  Gregory Peck  (  1916–2003 ). The name has traditionally been popular in Scotland, where it is often found in the form  <b>Gregor</b> ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"'Long","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["1  ♀, ♂ ‘Understanding’ or ‘compassion’.","2  ♀ ‘Tinkle’, in particular the tinkling sound of pieces of jade hanging in the wind. For the significance of jade in Chinese culture,  see  Yu   1."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Legs'","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Leslie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Leslie","meanings":["Transferred use of the Scottish surname derived from the lands of <i>Lesslyn</i> in Aberdeenshire (a place name perhaps named in Gaelic as <i>leas cuilinn</i> ‘garden of hollies’). Surnames and clan names have been used as given names more readily and from an earlier date in Scotland than elsewhere, and this is the name of an ancient family, who in the 14th and 15th centuries were close associates of the Scottish royal house of Stewart and who have held the earldom of Rothes since  1457 . The British film actor  Leslie Howard  (  1890–1943 ), who was of Hungarian origin, had a considerable influence on the popularity of the name, especially in the United States, where he appeared in Gone with the Wind (  1939 ). A famous female bearer is the French film actress  Leslie Caron  (  b. 1931 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir Gregory 'Long Legs' de Dundee was born in 1210, in Dundee, Forfarshire, Scotland as the son of Albert de Dundee. He had at least 1 son. He died in 1278, in his hometown, at the age of 68, and was buried in Dundee, Forfarshire, Scotland."},"et":{"1210–1278":"1210–1278","1225–1285":"1225–1285","1255–1307":"1255–1307","1190–1250":"1190–1250","1190":"1190","Abt 1250":"umbes 1250","1225":"1225","1278":"1278","1255":"1255","1210":"1210","1285":"1285","1250":"1250","1307":"1307","Dundee City, Scotland":"Dundee, Forfarshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1210–1278":"1210–1278","1225–1285":"1225–1285","1255–1307":"1255–1307","1190–1250":"1190–1250","1190":"1190","Abt 1250":"noin 1250","1225":"1225","1278":"1278","1255":"1255","1210":"1210","1285":"1285","1250":"1250","1307":"1307","Dundee City, Scotland":"Dundee, Forfarshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"1210–1278":"1210–1278","1225–1285":"1225–1285","1255–1307":"1255–1307","1190–1250":"1190–1250","1190":"1190","Abt 1250":"environ 1250","1225":"1225","1278":"1278","1255":"1255","1210":"1210","1285":"1285","1250":"1250","1307":"1307","Dundee City, Scotland":"Dundee, Forfarshire, Écosse","lifeSummary":"Sir Gregory 'Long Legs' de Dundee est né en 1210, à Dundee, Forfarshire, Écosse, fils de Albert de Dundee. Il a eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé en 1278, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 68 ans, et a été enterré à Dundee, Forfarshire, Écosse."},"de":{"1210–1278":"1210–1278","1225–1285":"1225–1285","1255–1307":"1255–1307","1190–1250":"1190–1250","1190":"1190","Abt 1250":"um 1250","1225":"1225","1278":"1278","1255":"1255","1210":"1210","1285":"1285","1250":"1250","1307":"1307","Dundee City, Scotland":"Dundee, Forfarshire, Scotland","lifeSummary":"Sir Gregory 'Long Legs' de Dundee wurde 1210 in Dundee, Forfarshire, Scotland, als S